CREATE TABLE `bigquery-public-data.geo_census_tracts.census_tracts_south_dakota`
(
  state_fips_code STRING OPTIONS(description="Two digit FIPS code that uniquely identifies each state. State names and their corresponding FIPS codes are available as a BigQuery Public Dataset: bigquery-public-data.census_fips_codes.states_2016"),
  county_fips_code STRING OPTIONS(description="Four-digit county FIPS code.   County names and their corresponding FIPS codes can be found in BigQuery: bigquery-public-data.census_fips_codes.counties_2016"),
  tract_ce STRING OPTIONS(description="Current Census tract code"),
  geo_id STRING OPTIONS(description="Census tract identifier; a concatenation of Current state FIPS code, county FIPS code, and census tract code"),
  tract_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Current census tract name, this is the census tract code converted to an integer or integer plus 2- character decimal if the last two characters of the code are not both zeros."),
  lsad_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Current translated legal/statistical area description and the census tract name"),
  functional_status STRING OPTIONS(description="Current functional status of the Census tract"),
  area_land_meters INT64 OPTIONS(description="Current land area, in square meters"),
  area_water_meters INT64 OPTIONS(description="Current water area, in square meters"),
  internal_point_lat STRING OPTIONS(description="Latitude of the state's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the state's geographic center"),
  internal_point_lon STRING OPTIONS(description="Longitude of the state's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the state's geographic center"),
  internal_point_geo GEOGRAPHY OPTIONS(description="Geographic representation of the state's internal point, which is the point at or closest to the tract's geographic center"),
  tract_geom GEOGRAPHY OPTIONS(description="Geographical representation of the polygon that defines the perimeter of each Census tract. This column should be used as the GEO column for visualization in BigQuery Geo Viz")
);
